  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nfeature\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nSee issue #15527 . `__reactEventHandlers` will save its latest updated version of props which contain `children`. Since a lot of nodes will not always update they may hold a very old version of `children`.\r\n\r\nI guess it's useless, so I update the `updateFiberProps` function to this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nexport function updateFiberProps(node, props) {\r\n  const newProps = {\r\n    ...props,\r\n    children: null,\r\n  };\r\n  node[internalEventHandlersKey] = newProps;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nand I run all the tests, all passed.\r\n\r\nIs there any reason we can't get rid of the `children` saved on native element node?\r\n",
